==Starting out==
===Juliet===
====First talk====
* {{topt|Ask about the birthday party.}}
** '''Juliet:''' Oh, I just can't be bothered.
** '''Player:''' What's the matter Juliet?
** '''Juliet:''' I've been told I have to throw the birthday party at my place this year, but I don't feel like it, my life is just tragic.
** '''Juliet:''' I don't care about this party.
** '''Player:''' Sometimes I think my life's nothing but a comedy, but I don't let it get me down. Why so glum chum?
** {{tcond|If the player has not completed [[Romeo & Juliet]]:}}
*** '''Juliet:''' I have no-one in my life, I can't be with my love, Romeo. There is nothing for me to wake up to each day, I feel like my life is a repeat of the same day over and over.
*** '''Player:''' You need to get out and enjoy life Juliet, slay some dragons and explore the world.
*** '''Juliet:''' I wouldn't go that far! I'm just tired of being locked in this house with just my cousin, Phillipa.
*** '''Juliet:''' The only thing that cheers me up is looking over to Gertrude's house and seeing her kittens playing.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the player has completed [[Romeo & Juliet]]:}}
*** '''Juliet:''' Romeo doesn't care for me anymore, the minute he saw Phillipa, he's been all over her. I have no one anymore.
*** '''Player:''' Oh come on, it can't be that bad. Is Romeo really worth getting this upset over? He's a bit empty headed if you ask me.
*** '''Juliet:''' He was all I had, now the only thing keeping me going is the soft sounds of Gertrude's Cats.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** '''Player:''' Sounds like you need a new friend, would you like me to see if Gertrude will give you one of her kittens?
** '''Juliet:''' I've asked her before, but we aren't on good standing anymore, ever since I planted lilies in our garden.
** '''Player:''' Why would she be upset about lilies?
** '''Juliet:''' They're quite poisonous to cats, how was I supposed to know, I'm not a cat doctor...
** '''Player:''' Maybe getting you a pet isn't a good idea then, perhaps I should go talk to your cousin for some ideas.
** '''Juliet:''' I'll be here...alone, waiting for the next adventurer to come along and try to help.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|event=No|Something else.}}

====When talked to again====
* {{topt|Ask about the birthday party.}}
** {{trandom}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 1}}
*** '''Juliet:''' Love's stories written in love's richest books. To fan the moonbeams from his sleeping eyes.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 2}}
*** '''Juliet:''' Did my heart love till now? Forswear it, sight! For I ne'er saw true beauty till this night.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 3}}
*** '''Juliet:''' All the world's a stage, And all the men and women merely players. They have their exits and their entrances. And one man in his time plays many parts,
*** '''Juliet:''' His acts being seven ages.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 4}}
*** '''Juliet:''' Double, double, toil and trouble. Fire burn, and cauldron bubble!
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 5}}
*** '''Juliet:''' Doubt thou the stars are fire. Doubt that the sun doth move. Doubt truth to be a liar. But never doubt I love.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 6}}
*** '''Juliet:''' All that glitters is not platinum.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** '''Player:''' What are you mumbling to yourself Juliet?
** '''Juliet:''' Oh, I've just been reading a book, it helps me get through the day.
** '''Player:''' I need to find a way to cheer her up, Phillipa should be able to help, I just can't stand to see her like this.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|event=No|Something else.}}

===Phillipa===
====First talk====
* {{topt|Ask about the birthday party.}}
** {{tcond|If the player has not completed [[Romeo & Juliet]]:}}
*** '''Player:''' Hi, could you help me cheer up Juliet?
*** '''Phillipa:''' Sure, I'll be happy to, what's wrong with her?
*** '''Player:''' Well she's been feeling down, she mentioned not being able to be with some guy called Romeo and her father has put her in charge of this years birthday party.
*** '''Phillipa:''' Romeo! Oh, he's so dreamy, a little bit annoying, but dreamy.
*** '''Player:''' Okay, thanks for sharing, but I need to get her started on the birthday party or there won't be one this year.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the player has completed [[Romeo & Juliet]]:}}
*** '''Player:''' Hey Phillipa, we need to do something about Juliet.
*** '''Phillipa:''' Hi [player name], good to see you again, how are you?
*** '''Player:''' Hi... I'm good thanks.
*** '''Phillipa:''' Oh that's great! Romeo and I are also doing great thanks for asking, we've been having the best time since you introduced me to him.
*** '''Player:''' I'm not here to find out how you and Romeo are getting on, I'm here to help Juliet.
*** '''Phillipa:''' Typical, what is she upset about this time?
*** '''Player:''' Her father put her in charge of the birthday party this year, but she's not feeling up to it, recent events have got her feeling quite down.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** '''Phillipa:''' Why don't you try cheering her up?
** '''Player:''' I offered to get her one of Gertrude's cats, but she told me there's little chance of that happening.
** '''Phillipa:''' Hmm, why don't you try dressing up as one, you could be her emotional support human.
** '''Player:''' That sounds like a terrible idea...
** '''Player:''' Surely there's something less... weird... I can do instead?
** '''Phillipa:''' Got any better ideas?
** '''Player:''' ... no.
** '''Phillipa:''' Thought not, so since she loves cats, why don't you dress up as one and dance for her.
** '''Player:''' I'm not going to dress up as a cat...
** '''Phillipa:''' Fine, but what about just the ears?
** '''Player:''' ... I suppose I can do that.
** '''Player:''' Where am I supposed to find some? I'm not about to take some off a cat.
** '''Phillipa:''' I'm sure Iffie in town could put something together for you, she stays in the clothing store by Varrock Square.
** '''Player:''' Fine, I'll go have a word.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|event=No|Something else.}}

====When talked to again====
* {{topt|Ask about the birthday party.}}
** '''Phillipa:''' How are you getting on with your cat costume?
** '''Player:''' Still working on it, who did you say could help me with it?
** '''Phillipa:''' Iffie should be able to help, she runs the clothing store by Varrock Square.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|event=No|Something else.}}

===Gertrude===
