==Getting the cat ears==
===Iffie===
====First talk====
* '''Player:''' Hello Ma'am, are you Iffie?
* '''Iffie:''' Yes dearie, what can I do for you?
* '''Player:''' Phillipa told me that you could make me a pair of cat ears.
* '''Iffie:''' Cat ears? That's a bit cringe isn't it dearie?
* '''Player:''' It's not for me...it's for a friend.
* '''Iffie:''' Well I never...back in my day...
* '''Player:''' I don't like it either, but I don't have much choice. Do you think you could make some for me?
* '''Iffie:''' I suppose I could, but you'll need to help me dear.
* '''Player:''' Of course, what do you need me to do?
* '''Iffie:''' To make them properly, I'll need you to get me some cat fur.
* '''Player:''' No way, I did not sign up for this so I could skin a cat.
* '''Iffie:''' Hehehe, no dearie, there's more than one way to shave a cat.
* '''Iffie:''' The most obvious place that comes to mind, is Miss, oh... what's her name... ... Gertrude's house in West Varrock.
* '''Iffie:''' She should be able to help you, might confuse the poor girl if you ask her directly though.
* '''Player:''' Thanks Iffie, I'll see what I can find.
* {{tact|end}}

====When talked to again====
* '''Player:''' I'm struggling to find some cat hair.
* '''Iffie:''' I have better things to do than help you all day.
* '''Iffie:''' Check Getrude's{{sic}} house, opposite Juliet's, she must have plenty left on her clothes over the years.
* '''Player:''' Thanks again Iffie, sorry for taking up your precious time.
* {{tact|end}}

